President Obama has announced the Presidential Delegation that will attend the Opening Ceremony of the 2016 Olympic Summer Games in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. The delegation will attend athletic events, meet with U.S. athletes, and attend the Opening Ceremony. Secretary of State John Kerry will lead the delegation, which includes U.S. Ambassador to Brazil Liliana Ayalde, Acting Assistant Secretary of State for Western Hemisphere Affairs Mari Carmen Aponte, White House Deputy Communications Director Liz Allen, Director of the White House Visitors Office Ellie Schafer, and Olympic gold medalist Mark Spitz.